Soft-landing support service in Mexico for Guatemalan companies after learning about 
Florida’s business development models;

A strategic plan for the Logistics Sector in the State of Hidalgo, Mexico, in 
collaboration with Georgia Institute of Technology;
A training program in Tucumán, Argentina, related to Spatial Missions and Satellites 
Production with support from the Brazilian Company Orbital Engenharia;
Replication of the Tallahassee-based SciGirls program in Belize to create the “SciGirl 
Saturday” program which encourages girls to engage in Science, Technology, 
Engineering and Mathematics (STEM);

12 entrepreneurship clubs in Haiti’s high schools inspired by Flagler County School 
District model;

A Business Services Center in Ecuador after visiting Packard Place in North Carolina;

A training to support female driven businesses with the support of the Young Leaders 
of the Americas Initiative (YLAI) alumni and the U.S. Embassy in the Port of Spain, 
Trinidad and Tobago;

Establishment of a Memorandum of Understanding between Argentina and Germany 
for joint funding of research and development projects of small-and-medium-sized 
enterprises;

Expansion of the Creative Business Cup Innovation Competition in Guatemala and 
Haiti led by an NGO in Paraguay; 

Formal incorporation of EMBRAPII Brazil as part of the CORNET German Network to 
advance collective SME research projects;

Training exchanges for medical doctors between the Government of Tucumán 
Argentina and Israel.
